snippet.textDisplay:
I loved the first round of silence.
I don't relate much to the "needing energy to recharge" definition of being an introvert (though it happens to me sometimes) as most people on here and beyond. I relate way more to the definition that describes an introvert as being shy, quiet, socially awkward at times (like at parties, or infront of people in general). I am not a talkative person, I do keep to myself a lot (not in a creepy, anti-social way but I guess some see it that way, yikes), I do enjoy my own company, and being in nature. Welp. I know I'm in the minority with this and I'm cool with it.

snippet.textDisplay:
I feel like most people confuse Confident Introverts with being Extroverted and Shy Extroverts as being Introverted.

I'm a shy extrovert, I get energy from being with/around people, but I'm so shy that I wont approach them first.
On the opposite side my best friend is a confident introvert, she approached me first and thats how we became friends, but sometimes when I wanna hang out (and trust me I wanna hangout 24/7) she says she needs time for herself which is totally okay!
People really need to know that introverts and extroverts don't have just a set list of stereotypical characteristics. We're all unique humans!
